{
  "texts": [
    "The trilemma suggests that there is often a trade-off between these three fundamental aspects of blockchain technology, meaning that improving one aspect may come at the expense of the others.",
    "Security guarantees the system's immutability and resistance to assaults, while scalability takes care of the system's capacity to handle transactions.",
    "Decentralization enables the system to be faulttolerant and attack-resistant.Traditional blockchain networks have inherent limitations on the number of transactions they can process per second.",
    "For instance, Bitcoin handles around 7 transactions per second, and Ethereum around 15-45 TPS (Transactions Per Second) [40].",
    "Scalability issues can lead to longer confirmation times for transactions."
  ]
}